WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-DE

00:00:00.200 --> 00:00:01.334
In "Return of the Ancients"

00:00:01.334 --> 00:00:05.672
we
added a series of challenges to Path of Exile 2 for the first time.

00:00:05.672 --> 00:00:07.574
For every two completed challenges,

00:00:07.574 --> 00:00:10.193
you will receive a piece of the
"Knights of Aldur" armor set,

00:00:10.193 --> 00:00:11.795
so give it a try.

00:00:12.362 --> 00:00:15.148
To see your progress and requirements for
completing challenges,

00:00:15.148 --> 00:00:17.801
simply press "H" to open the window.

00:00:17.951 --> 00:00:19.319
There are a total of eight challenges,

00:00:19.319 --> 00:00:22.222
ranging from fairly easy to
fairly difficult.

00:00:22.222 --> 00:00:23.923
To complete "The Rune Seeker",

00:00:23.923 --> 00:00:26.626
you must find relics with an increasing
number of slots

00:00:26.626 --> 00:00:28.595
and use them to craft
items.

00:00:29.229 --> 00:00:32.999
Crafting with seven slots can
be difficult with six waves of opponents,

00:00:32.999 --> 00:00:36.002
so you
should be well prepared for this fight.  There are

00:00:38.638 --> 00:00:39.639


00:00:39.639 --> 00:00:41.408
many optional bosses throughout the campaign.

00:00:41.408 --> 00:00:42.959
To complete "The Hunter",

00:00:42.959 --> 00:00:45.361
you must defeat six of them.

00:00:45.361 --> 00:00:49.282
The last two, "Akthi, the Last Sting"
and "Anundr, the Sandworm",

00:00:49.282 --> 00:00:51.551
can be a little difficult to find in the Khari Crossing
.

00:00:52.185 --> 00:00:55.271
Follow the riverbed to
locate them.

00:00:55.388 --> 00:00:57.073
You'll find their arena at the end.

00:00:58.558 --> 00:01:00.877
For "The Ascendant"
you need all eight points

00:01:00.877 --> 00:01:03.880
of your Ascendance class by
completing all Ascendance exams.

00:01:03.880 --> 00:01:06.766
 
Getting those last two points can be quite challenging.  To do

00:01:06.766 --> 00:01:10.220
this, you must either defeat Zarokh in the fourth level
of the Sekhemas Trial,

00:01:10.653 --> 00:01:14.390
or the Trial Master in the Trial of Chaos
by finding all three keys.

00:01:15.141 --> 00:01:16.960
Of the two, the Trial of Chaos will take

00:01:16.960 --> 00:01:20.029
much longer, as you have to complete the trial several
times,

00:01:20.029 --> 00:01:22.549
but the Trial of Sekhemas
is much more challenging.

00:01:22.549 --> 00:01:25.151
It is therefore up to you which
path you want to take.

00:01:26.719 --> 00:01:28.138
"The Reliquary" is simple.

00:01:28.138 --> 00:01:30.573
Identifies 50 different
unique items.

00:01:32.025 --> 00:01:33.910
You just can't find any?

00:01:33.910 --> 00:01:37.647
Jado, the master of the Atlas, has many skills
that will help you find them.

00:01:39.749 --> 00:01:41.151
To complete "The Artisan,"

00:01:41.151 --> 00:01:43.720
you will need to use several different crafting items


00:01:43.720 --> 00:01:45.839
obtained from relic encounters.

00:01:47.240 --> 00:01:48.441
For "The Cartographer"

00:01:48.441 --> 00:01:50.894
you need to assign your entire atlas tree.

00:01:51.177 --> 00:01:52.712
All 300 points.

00:01:53.163 --> 00:01:56.883
Either you choose the slow route and
complete all the maps within the fortress.

00:01:56.916 --> 00:01:58.918
Or you can choose the other path.

00:01:58.918 --> 00:02:01.054
Each time you defeat the "Judge of Divinity,"


00:02:01.054 --> 00:02:05.175
you will be given the opportunity to
automatically complete a large area of ​​the fortress.

00:02:06.676 --> 00:02:09.679
The keys to this battle can
be found in citadels in the Atlas.

00:02:09.829 --> 00:02:12.832
Each one is marked with a beam
that you can see through the fog.

00:02:13.032 --> 00:02:16.719
After you have defeated the final boss four times,
the entire fortress will be completed.

00:02:17.871 --> 00:02:21.040
And then we have
"The Conqueror."

00:02:21.391 --> 00:02:24.010
This challenge requires
killing three final bosses,

00:02:24.010 --> 00:02:25.478
the most difficult fights in the game.

00:02:25.979 --> 00:02:27.030
Tangmazu,

00:02:27.030 --> 00:02:28.097
the Bodach

00:02:28.097 --> 00:02:29.682
and the Vessel of Kulemak.

00:02:30.083 --> 00:02:34.070
These are the final bosses of the Delirium,
Ritual, and Abyss leagues,

00:02:34.070 --> 00:02:37.190
so you will need to
complete all three quest lines for this challenge.

00:02:37.674 --> 00:02:39.909
Speaking of "Vessel of Kulemak",

00:02:39.909 --> 00:02:42.162
you have to defeat this boss on the highest
difficulty level.

00:02:42.162 --> 00:02:44.113
This means you have to risk the item
during the fight

00:02:44.113 --> 00:02:46.716
by putting the finger back
and defeating him anyway.

00:02:49.352 --> 00:02:50.303
As mentioned previously,

00:02:50.303 --> 00:02:53.223
you will receive pieces of the armor set for every two completed challenges
,

00:02:53.223 --> 00:02:55.675
so you don't have to complete them all
to receive rewards.

00:02:55.675 --> 00:02:58.628
But if you manage it,
you can show off,

00:02:58.778 --> 00:03:02.715
because everyone in the global chat or forums can see
how many challenges you have completed.

00:03:03.149 --> 00:03:05.835
You will also receive the Totem
Hideout decoration for your hideout,

00:03:05.835 --> 00:03:07.837
so that all players who trade with you
can see

00:03:07.837 --> 00:03:10.840
how well you have done in this league
.

00:03:11.191 --> 00:03:15.361
Try these challenges and more
on May 29th in "Return of the Ancients".

00:03:15.562 --> 00:03:17.463
Thanks for watching and see you later!

